mulberry (4.1.0a3-git-20260304-0035) unstable; urgency=medium

  IMPORTANT: Modernization Changes

  This version represents a major modernization of Mulberry for current
  Linux systems. Users upgrading from older builds should be aware of
  the following significant changes:

  * OpenSSL 3.x Compatibility
    - Rebuilt against OpenSSL 3.x instead of legacy OpenSSL 1.0
    - All SSL/TLS functionality verified working with modern libraries
    - Certificate validation now uses system CA certificate store

  * 64-bit Native Build
    - This is a native 64-bit build (x86_64)
    - Preferences files from 32-bit builds should migrate automatically
    - If you experience preferences corruption, remove ~/.mulberry/preferences.mbp
      and reconfigure from scratch

  * Desktop Integration
    - Mulberry now appears in application menus under Network > Email
    - Registered as system handler for mailto: and webcal: URLs
    - Click email addresses in other applications to compose in Mulberry

  * Timezone Database
    - Calendar timezone data now automatically updated from IANA tzdata
    - Improves accuracy of calendar scheduling across time zones

  * Clipboard Improvements
    - Fixed paste of UTF-8 text from modern applications
    - Eliminated CRLF mojibake when pasting from some sources

  * Known Limitations
    - Upstream development appears to be very limited
    - Some modern email features (OAuth2 authentication, etc.) not supported
    - Users with modern requirements should consider Thunderbird or Evolution

  For detailed technical changes, see /usr/share/doc/mulberry/changelog.gz

 -- yitzhaq <github@anonmail.uk>  Wed, 04 Mar 2026 00:35:18 +0100
